      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Testing conducted under at least two distinct loading rates or environmental conditions to characterize condition sensitivity.",
      "rationale": "All testing was performed at a single crosshead displacement rate (5 mm/min) per ASTM F1717 protocol. No alternative loading rates or simulated physiological fluid environments were evaluated. This limits characterization of condition sensitivity; achieved level is Gradation 2, one below the required Gradation 3. This shortfall is noted and accepted given the quasi-static nature of the intended use and the low strain-rate sensitivity of Ti-6Al-4V ELI."
    },
